1
00:01:00,167 --> 00:01:02,909
[Episode 22: By the Book]

2
00:01:16,250 --> 00:01:18,440
He's not here.

3
00:01:18,440 --> 00:01:20,725
Out for lunch?

4
00:01:26,625 --> 00:01:28,667
Writer Kim.

5
00:01:28,667 --> 00:01:30,833
Oh, you're already here!

6
00:01:30,833 --> 00:01:32,042
Hello.

7
00:01:32,042 --> 00:01:35,356
You're early. Wasn't the meeting at one?

8
00:01:35,356 --> 00:01:37,981
There was no traffic at all.

9
00:01:37,981 --> 00:01:39,833
Did I show up too soon?

10
00:01:39,833 --> 00:01:41,417
No, not at all.

11
00:01:41,417 --> 00:01:43,333
The details haven't been set yet,

12
00:01:43,333 --> 00:01:46,208
so feel free to let us know what you'd like.

13
00:01:46,208 --> 00:01:48,667
We'll make it work.

14
00:01:48,667 --> 00:01:50,166
I don't know the first thing about this.

15
00:01:50,166 --> 00:01:52,125
You're the one who knows best.

16
00:01:52,125 --> 00:01:55,583
You really need to pay closer attention
to these things now.

17
00:01:55,583 --> 00:01:59,417
You're not that rookie writer anymore.

18
00:01:59,417 --> 00:02:02,125
I'm still the same person I've always been.

19
00:02:02,125 --> 00:02:06,058
Come on, even your presence is different now...

20
00:02:08,958 --> 00:02:10,148
But anyway...

21
00:02:10,148 --> 00:02:12,892
You're looking especially great today.

22
00:02:13,981 --> 00:02:16,542
Did something good happen?

23
00:02:16,542 --> 00:02:17,608
Sorry?

24
00:02:17,608 --> 00:02:21,132
Oh, it's nothing special, really...

25
00:02:21,786 --> 00:02:22,833
By the way...

26
00:02:22,833 --> 00:02:25,471
Soon Rok...

27
00:02:25,471 --> 00:02:27,523
How's...

28
00:02:27,523 --> 00:02:29,142
Sorry?

29
00:02:30,898 --> 00:02:33,940
Is he keeping it together? No trouble?

30
00:02:33,940 --> 00:02:36,417
Oh, yeah, he's doing fine.

31
00:02:36,417 --> 00:02:38,523
That's a relief.

32
00:02:38,523 --> 00:02:41,648
If there's even the slightest thing
bothering you,

33
00:02:41,648 --> 00:02:42,958
don't hesitate to say so.

34
00:02:42,958 --> 00:02:46,356
I've been keeping a close eye on him lately.

35
00:02:46,356 --> 00:02:47,667
How come?

36
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:50,500
His attitude lately has been driving me crazy.

37
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:53,000
He didn't use to be like this.
Kid's gotten too big for his boots.

38
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,606
He's doing well on our team,
so don't worry about it.

39
00:02:56,606 --> 00:02:59,917
I'm only putting up with it
because he's someone I care about.

40
00:02:59,917 --> 00:03:01,898
But lately, I swear...

41
00:03:01,898 --> 00:03:03,833
Oh, speak of the devil.

42
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:05,773
There he is, right on cue.

43
00:03:05,773 --> 00:03:07,250
<i>It's Soon Rok!</i>

44
00:03:07,250 --> 00:03:10,808
<i>Soon Rok, did you eat?</i>

45
00:03:13,458 --> 00:03:17,167
Writer Kim got here a while ago.
Where have you been?

46
00:03:17,167 --> 00:03:18,958
Oh, Writer Kim, you're here.

47
00:03:18,958 --> 00:03:20,975
Yes.

48
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:32,917
Can I get you more coffee?

49
00:03:32,917 --> 00:03:34,767
I'm fine, thanks.

50
00:03:38,106 --> 00:03:40,065
The production team are on their way up.

51
00:03:40,065 --> 00:03:41,773
They'll be here shortly.

52
00:03:41,773 --> 00:03:43,475
Okay.

53
00:03:45,398 --> 00:03:47,350
Actually...

54
00:03:47,940 --> 00:03:49,558
Yes?

55
00:03:54,315 --> 00:03:56,392
You look really pretty today, noona.

56
00:04:00,667 --> 00:04:03,083
I'm always like this, though.

57
00:04:03,083 --> 00:04:04,583
This is just how I look.

58
00:04:04,583 --> 00:04:07,017
Someone's a little full of herself.

59
00:04:26,273 --> 00:04:28,542
Hey, Soon Rok.

60
00:04:28,542 --> 00:04:32,100
Shouldn't we tell the Editor about us?

61
00:04:34,065 --> 00:04:35,531
About us dating?

62
00:04:36,792 --> 00:04:40,583
If he finds out later,
he's really going to feel betrayed.

63
00:04:40,583 --> 00:04:42,375
I'll tell I Da too,

64
00:04:42,375 --> 00:04:44,375
so you should be the one
to talk to the Editor...

65
00:04:44,375 --> 00:04:45,958
That's out of the question.

66
00:04:45,958 --> 00:04:47,523
If he finds out,

67
00:04:47,523 --> 00:04:50,065
I might get kicked out of the editorial team.

68
00:04:50,065 --> 00:04:51,333
Oh, come on. Really?

69
00:04:51,333 --> 00:04:52,398
I'm serious.

70
00:04:52,398 --> 00:04:54,767
There's something I said before.

71
00:05:00,042 --> 00:05:01,940
<i>You know, sometimes...</i>

72
00:05:01,940 --> 00:05:03,387
<i>these PDs who can't separate work
from their personal life</i>

73
00:05:03,387 --> 00:05:05,792
<i>and date their own writers</i>

74
00:05:05,792 --> 00:05:07,167
<i>are just embarrassing.</i>

75
00:05:07,167 --> 00:05:08,398
<i>Like, how are you supposed to</i>

76
00:05:08,398 --> 00:05:11,500
<i>stay objective about the work?</i>

77
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:13,083
So what did you say?

78
00:05:13,083 --> 00:05:14,708
What was your take?

79
00:05:14,708 --> 00:05:16,440
<i>Anyone who does that</i>

80
00:05:16,440 --> 00:05:18,565
<i>has no business calling themselves a PD.</i>

81
00:05:18,565 --> 00:05:21,250
<i>You think so, too?</i>

82
00:05:21,250 --> 00:05:22,500
<i>People like that</i>

83
00:05:22,500 --> 00:05:25,500
<i>shouldn't be anywhere near the editorial team.</i>

84
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:28,083
And back in Busan too...

85
00:05:28,083 --> 00:05:29,850
<i>Go on.</i>

86
00:05:31,542 --> 00:05:33,148
<i>Using personal feelings</i>

87
00:05:33,148 --> 00:05:35,356
<i>to take advantage of a colleague writer
just isn't right.</i>

88
00:05:35,356 --> 00:05:38,856
<i>How is that taking advantage?
He was just showing interest.</i>

89
00:05:38,856 --> 00:05:41,440
<i>And I backed him up.
Does that make me guilty too?</i>

90
00:05:41,440 --> 00:05:43,667
<i>People can act
on their feelings on a trip, you know.</i>

91
00:05:43,667 --> 00:05:46,167
<i>I don't think that's okay.</i>

92
00:05:46,167 --> 00:05:48,100
<i>It was a work workshop.</i>

93
00:05:48,958 --> 00:05:50,398
<i>You still have to keep things professional.</i>

94
00:05:50,398 --> 00:05:53,958
<i>Oh, Mr. Righteous has entered the building.</i>

95
00:05:53,958 --> 00:05:55,856
<i>Aren't you just perfect?</i>

96
00:05:55,856 --> 00:05:57,750
<i>Oh, like you've never</i>

97
00:05:57,750 --> 00:05:59,815
<i>dated anyone at work in your life.</i>

98
00:05:59,815 --> 00:06:01,190
<i>I actually haven't.</i>

99
00:06:01,190 --> 00:06:03,167
<i>So you've never even had a thing
with anyone there?</i>

100
00:06:03,167 --> 00:06:05,167
<i>I don't let that happen at work.</i>

101
00:06:05,167 --> 00:06:06,500
<i>- How come?
- What?</i>

102
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:07,875
<i>Why not? It's not like it's against the law.</i>

103
00:06:07,875 --> 00:06:09,750
<i>Nobody's breaking any rules here.</i>

104
00:06:09,750 --> 00:06:10,750
<i>It's my rule.</i>

105
00:06:10,750 --> 00:06:12,981
<i>Oh, spare me the rules.</i>

106
00:06:12,981 --> 00:06:14,292
<i>Just wait and see.</i>

107
00:06:14,292 --> 00:06:17,250
<i>The second I catch you with a thing going on,
you're done!</i>

108
00:06:17,250 --> 00:06:19,392
<i>That's never happening.</i>

109
00:06:20,083 --> 00:06:23,106
You really said all that?

110
00:06:23,106 --> 00:06:25,583
That's exactly why this can't happen.

111
00:06:25,583 --> 00:06:28,208
Why say something you couldn't keep?

112
00:06:28,208 --> 00:06:30,500
I was trying to keep it.

113
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:33,542
Is that why you kept your distance from me too?

114
00:06:33,542 --> 00:06:34,565
But even so,

115
00:06:34,565 --> 00:06:38,815
my irresistible charm just did you in, right?

116
00:06:38,815 --> 00:06:41,083
You had no choice but to break your own rule

117
00:06:41,083 --> 00:06:43,690
because of me.

118
00:06:43,690 --> 00:06:45,600
That's what happened, isn't it?

119
00:06:46,815 --> 00:06:50,231
The self-admiration is really something.

120
00:06:50,231 --> 00:06:52,350
And you're not denying it.

121
00:06:54,125 --> 00:06:55,148
Noona.

122
00:06:55,148 --> 00:06:56,901
Didn't you say you wanted to visit Kyoto?

123
00:06:56,901 --> 00:06:58,292
Yeah, why?

124
00:06:58,292 --> 00:07:00,917
Let's do a quick overnight trip,
Friday and Saturday.

125
00:07:00,917 --> 00:07:03,440
Saturday's your birthday, noona.

126
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:05,815
Are you serious?

127
00:07:05,815 --> 00:07:07,292
I'm definitely in, but...

128
00:07:07,292 --> 00:07:09,565
- I'll get the tickets then.
- Wait, weren't you...

129
00:07:09,565 --> 00:07:13,208
supposed to be back
from your China trip on Friday?

130
00:07:13,208 --> 00:07:14,958
And you've got another trip
right after next week.

131
00:07:14,958 --> 00:07:17,875
I'll just transfer straight
to another flight at the airport.

132
00:07:17,875 --> 00:07:19,833
That sounds like too much.

133
00:07:19,833 --> 00:07:22,042
I'm fine. We can always go another time.

134
00:07:22,042 --> 00:07:23,125
No, we can't.

135
00:07:23,125 --> 00:07:25,083
Going on a trip after your birthday

136
00:07:25,083 --> 00:07:27,167
isn't a birthday gift anymore.

137
00:07:27,167 --> 00:07:28,255
Why's that?

138
00:07:28,255 --> 00:07:31,208
Is that one of Soon Rok's principles?

139
00:07:31,208 --> 00:07:32,250
Fine by me.

140
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:34,339
I can get behind that rule.

141
00:07:35,417 --> 00:07:37,042
Then let's go on a trip.

142
00:07:40,708 --> 00:07:41,815
You're here!

143
00:07:41,815 --> 00:07:43,625
- Oh, yes, come on in.
- You're here.

144
00:07:43,625 --> 00:07:45,333
- Hi there.
- Hello.

145
00:07:45,333 --> 00:07:48,106
- Hello.
- Hello.

146
00:07:48,106 --> 00:07:49,850
<i>That's right.</i>

147
00:07:51,523 --> 00:07:54,725
<i>If Yumi's village has Writer Cell's castle,</i>

148
00:07:58,208 --> 00:08:02,142
<i>Soon Rok's village has something just as grand.</i>

149
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:07,142
<i>Its name...</i>

150
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:10,434
<i>The Tower of Principles.</i>

151
00:08:12,292 --> 00:08:14,850
<i>It stands as the symbol of Soon Rok's village.</i>

152
00:08:16,690 --> 00:08:19,625
<i>Built over 29 years from the principles
Soon Rok established,</i>

153
00:08:19,625 --> 00:08:21,833
<i>each block holds a rule of its own,</i>

154
00:08:21,833 --> 00:08:23,798
<i>big or small,</i>

155
00:08:23,798 --> 00:08:26,750
<i>significant or trivial.</i>

156
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:29,500
[Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang
is the only way to go for bungeoppang]

157
00:08:29,500 --> 00:08:32,083
<i>Lately, the tower has been under threat.</i>

158
00:08:32,083 --> 00:08:34,083
<i>Laundry on Wednesdays.</i>

159
00:08:34,083 --> 00:08:36,250
<i>What's going on?</i>

160
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:37,856
<i>Writer Kim.</i>

161
00:08:37,856 --> 00:08:41,458
<i>Want to watch the movie together?</i>

162
00:08:41,458 --> 00:08:43,750
<i>Don't go to the movies alone with someone</i>

163
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:46,208
<i>you don't have romantic feelings for.</i>

164
00:08:46,208 --> 00:08:49,100
<i>A broken principle has to be discarded...</i>

165
00:08:51,208 --> 00:08:52,208
<i>You are amazing.</i>

166
00:08:52,208 --> 00:08:56,017
<i>Do not offer any appraisal
of a writer other than their work.</i>

167
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:07,225
<i>Don't share an umbrella
with a woman you work with.</i>

168
00:09:13,190 --> 00:09:15,083
Hold on.

169
00:09:15,083 --> 00:09:16,792
Just wait a second!

170
00:09:16,792 --> 00:09:18,731
You can't just pull those out.

171
00:09:18,731 --> 00:09:21,267
The tower might start to shake.

172
00:09:27,583 --> 00:09:29,981
Look at it. It's wobbling!

173
00:09:29,981 --> 00:09:32,231
I know.

174
00:09:32,231 --> 00:09:35,225
But a principle that's been broken

175
00:09:37,375 --> 00:09:40,440
has to be thrown out. That's the rule.

176
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:43,333
This is a crisis though.

177
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:45,977
Soon Rok's principles never get broken.

178
00:09:45,977 --> 00:09:48,315
How many is that now,

179
00:09:48,315 --> 00:09:50,683
all because of Writer Kim?

180
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:54,683
This is why drawing the line matters.

181
00:09:58,042 --> 00:10:01,308
<i>But the crisis didn't stop there.</i>

182
00:10:06,292 --> 00:10:09,350
<i>Never cancel plans at the last minute.</i>

183
00:10:11,375 --> 00:10:14,125
<i>Don't fight during work.</i>

184
00:10:14,125 --> 00:10:16,292
<i>I think I might</i>

185
00:10:16,292 --> 00:10:20,083
<i>have feelings for you.</i>

186
00:10:20,083 --> 00:10:23,850
<i>Don't confess to a woman
you have a professional relationship with.</i>

187
00:10:32,750 --> 00:10:34,458
He's lost it, he's really lost it.

188
00:10:34,458 --> 00:10:36,500
Confessing to a writer, of all people!

189
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:37,848
If that one comes out,

190
00:10:37,848 --> 00:10:39,208
- the whole thing's coming down.
- Isn't it going to collapse?

191
00:10:39,208 --> 00:10:41,183
Watch out!

192
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:12,231
Any more, and it's too risky.

193
00:11:12,231 --> 00:11:15,375
One more missing
and this whole thing could fall apart.

194
00:11:15,375 --> 00:11:17,500
Do something about Writer Kim!

195
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:18,958
We already drew the line.

196
00:11:18,958 --> 00:11:21,375
We even went through the removal surgery.
What more do you want?

197
00:11:21,375 --> 00:11:22,815
Rational Cell!

198
00:11:22,815 --> 00:11:25,075
Look at Soon Rok!

199
00:11:25,833 --> 00:11:28,081
<i>No matter how I think about it,</i>

200
00:11:30,708 --> 00:11:32,725
<i>I like you, Writer Kim.</i>

201
00:11:33,458 --> 00:11:36,183
<i>It's pathetic I only realized now,</i>

202
00:11:36,875 --> 00:11:39,017
<i>but I think</i>

203
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:43,267
<i>I've liked you from the start.</i>

204
00:11:46,648 --> 00:11:51,142
<i>Don't go after a woman
who's already turned you down.</i>

205
00:11:53,375 --> 00:11:56,292
He went back to Writer Kim again.

206
00:11:56,292 --> 00:11:58,426
[Don't go after a woman
who's already turned you down]

207
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:09,042
- It's falling, it's coming down!
- No!

208
00:12:14,708 --> 00:12:17,200
[Don't go after a woman
who's already turned you down]

209
00:12:27,208 --> 00:12:29,138
[Cap your stanning budget
at 500,000 won a month]

210
00:12:31,065 --> 00:12:33,058
No!

211
00:12:47,750 --> 00:12:49,708
Just look at this disaster!

212
00:12:49,708 --> 00:12:51,292
In all of Soon Rok's 29 years,

213
00:12:51,292 --> 00:12:52,731
nothing like this has ever happened.

214
00:12:52,731 --> 00:12:55,000
The tower is on the verge of collapse.

215
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,625
I'm sorry.

216
00:12:56,625 --> 00:12:59,292
I've been drawing lines

217
00:12:59,292 --> 00:13:03,648
and going on blind dates
trying to keep my distance,

218
00:13:03,648 --> 00:13:07,208
but Writer Kim's pull is just too strong...

219
00:13:07,208 --> 00:13:08,875
Who is she, anyway?

220
00:13:08,875 --> 00:13:10,500
Is Writer Kim more important?

221
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:12,625
Or are the principles?

222
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:16,308
Soon Rok's principles are who Soon Rok is.

223
00:13:19,125 --> 00:13:22,665
He spent all 29 years building them up.

224
00:13:23,417 --> 00:13:25,558
If they fall,

225
00:13:26,690 --> 00:13:30,017
he isn't Soon Rok anymore!

226
00:13:32,417 --> 00:13:34,433
You're right.

227
00:13:35,458 --> 00:13:38,308
[Friday]

228
00:13:44,333 --> 00:13:46,224
Has he landed yet?

229
00:13:53,250 --> 00:13:55,065
Doesn't look like it.

230
00:13:55,065 --> 00:13:56,416
<i>Noona.</i>

231
00:13:57,917 --> 00:14:00,208
Oh, Soon Rok, you're here?

232
00:14:00,208 --> 00:14:02,065
Just touched down on the runway.

233
00:14:02,065 --> 00:14:03,750
I just got to the airport too.

234
00:14:03,750 --> 00:14:06,500
It's packed out here,
so let's meet inside after you check in.

235
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:09,208
I'll grab my bags and head straight there.

236
00:14:09,208 --> 00:14:12,142
Sure. I can't wait to see you.

237
00:14:14,648 --> 00:14:15,792
See you soon.

238
00:14:15,792 --> 00:14:16,817
<i>Yeah.</i>

239
00:14:16,817 --> 00:14:18,063
Okay.

240
00:14:21,125 --> 00:14:25,042
How long has it been?
It's almost been a whole week.

241
00:14:25,042 --> 00:14:27,971
<i>Hurry up! Let's get to Soon Rok already!</i>

242
00:14:27,971 --> 00:14:29,905
I'm on my way.

243
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,850
Thank you.

244
00:14:53,042 --> 00:14:55,083
<i>Noona, where are you?</i>

245
00:14:55,083 --> 00:14:57,017
<i>I've already boarded.</i>

246
00:15:03,250 --> 00:15:06,600
<i>I'm right by the gate. I'm heading in now.</i>

247
00:15:20,315 --> 00:15:22,356
It's been such a long time.

248
00:15:22,356 --> 00:15:25,333
Right, it's been forever.
Are you stopping by duty-free?

249
00:15:25,333 --> 00:15:28,517
- What's our gate number?
- Do you want to hit the duty-free shops?

250
00:15:31,333 --> 00:15:32,917
Oh, did you see that?

251
00:15:32,917 --> 00:15:35,625
Did you catch who just walked by?

252
00:15:35,625 --> 00:15:37,190
I didn't see anyone.

253
00:15:37,190 --> 00:15:39,148
Who was it? A celebrity?

254
00:15:39,148 --> 00:15:40,776
Who was it?

255
00:15:42,481 --> 00:15:44,933
Red alert!

256
00:15:54,856 --> 00:15:57,850
<i>Soon Rok, what do we do?</i>

257
00:16:02,856 --> 00:16:04,933
Soon Rok!

258
00:16:11,125 --> 00:16:13,398
What are the odds!

259
00:16:13,398 --> 00:16:14,750
Oh, hello.

260
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:17,250
Hold on a second. Ju Ho.

261
00:16:17,250 --> 00:16:18,933
Ju Ho.

262
00:16:20,190 --> 00:16:21,975
What?

263
00:16:24,708 --> 00:16:26,500
What is he doing here?

264
00:16:28,023 --> 00:16:29,500
- Gosh.
- Hello.

265
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:31,542
Hold on. What are you doing here?

266
00:16:31,542 --> 00:16:33,125
Where are you headed?

267
00:16:33,125 --> 00:16:36,375
Didn't you just report back from Shanghai?

268
00:16:36,375 --> 00:16:37,648
Oh, yeah.

269
00:16:37,648 --> 00:16:38,833
That's right.

270
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:40,981
So where are you off to now?

271
00:16:40,981 --> 00:16:42,815
Oh, it's just...

272
00:16:42,815 --> 00:16:44,125
Well...

273
00:16:44,125 --> 00:16:46,815
I had a trip already planned.

274
00:16:46,815 --> 00:16:49,440
So you're skipping home entirely
and heading straight out again?

275
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:52,600
I booked it a while back.

276
00:16:53,606 --> 00:16:54,750
I mean,

277
00:16:54,750 --> 00:16:57,667
does that make sense to you? I'm not following.

278
00:16:57,667 --> 00:16:59,875
He's young, he can do what he wants, right?

279
00:16:59,875 --> 00:17:01,292
Where are the two of you headed?

280
00:17:01,292 --> 00:17:03,625
Golf club, our regular trip.

281
00:17:03,625 --> 00:17:05,542
Sir, I'll check your seat for you.

282
00:17:05,542 --> 00:17:07,417
- Oh, of course.
- Yeah.

283
00:17:07,417 --> 00:17:09,042
Alright, we'll catch up later.

284
00:17:09,042 --> 00:17:11,017
Right, sure.

285
00:17:13,106 --> 00:17:15,542
- It's a window seat.
- Great.

286
00:17:15,542 --> 00:17:17,456
Oh, come on, slide in.

287
00:17:27,893 --> 00:17:29,417
So is he traveling solo?

288
00:17:29,417 --> 00:17:31,398
- You think he's alone?
- He looks like it.

289
00:17:31,398 --> 00:17:33,708
The seat next to him is empty.
Someone's joining him.

290
00:17:33,708 --> 00:17:35,292
- Who?
- Oh, take a wild guess.

291
00:17:35,292 --> 00:17:38,250
Skipping home after a work trip
just to catch this flight?

292
00:17:38,250 --> 00:17:39,667
There's only one person he'd do that for.

293
00:17:39,667 --> 00:17:42,940
Oh, so that's what's going on?

294
00:17:42,940 --> 00:17:45,042
He's got someone?

295
00:17:45,042 --> 00:17:46,356
But, since when though?

296
00:17:46,356 --> 00:17:48,208
So he gets to go on trips with a girl

297
00:17:48,208 --> 00:17:50,458
but won't let me have
even a little something going on?

298
00:17:50,458 --> 00:17:52,475
What a selfish jerk.

299
00:17:54,167 --> 00:17:55,208
<i>Soon Rok.</i>

300
00:17:55,208 --> 00:17:58,735
<i>Writer Ju Ho and the Editor
just got on our plane.</i>

301
00:17:58,735 --> 00:18:00,361
<i>What are we going to do?</i>

302
00:18:17,231 --> 00:18:21,208
No office dating, no getting caught.

303
00:18:21,208 --> 00:18:24,500
This is the most important rule
in Soon Rok's book.

304
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:26,308
Once this one falls,

305
00:18:27,958 --> 00:18:29,958
everything falls with it.

306
00:18:29,958 --> 00:18:32,517
The whole tower comes down.

307
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:43,042
Hello?

308
00:18:43,042 --> 00:18:44,083
<i>Noona.</i>

309
00:18:44,083 --> 00:18:45,500
<i>How come you're not boarding?</i>

310
00:18:45,500 --> 00:18:47,267
Those two already got on, right?

311
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,440
They did.

312
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:51,606
Out of every flight,
why did it have to be this one?

313
00:18:51,606 --> 00:18:52,856
It's better if I don't get on.

314
00:18:52,856 --> 00:18:54,292
Excuse me?

315
00:18:54,292 --> 00:18:57,398
Writer Ju Ho's on there too.
You'll never hear the end of it.

316
00:18:57,398 --> 00:18:59,792
- I'm skipping this one.
- Then what's your plan?

317
00:18:59,792 --> 00:19:02,333
<i>I'll catch the next one.
There are plenty of flights to Osaka.</i>

318
00:19:02,333 --> 00:19:03,833
No. Just hold on.

319
00:19:03,833 --> 00:19:06,417
- Then I'll get off right now and...
<i>- Soon Rok!</i>

320
00:19:06,417 --> 00:19:09,183
Meet me at the airport.
I'll head straight there.

321
00:19:10,773 --> 00:19:12,642
Hello? Noona.

322
00:19:16,356 --> 00:19:21,000
<i>Ara Airlines Flight 701 to Osaka
is now closing its doors.</i>

323
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:23,208
Sir, please take your seat.

324
00:19:23,208 --> 00:19:24,792
- My apologies.
- Hey.

325
00:19:24,792 --> 00:19:26,667
Look at him. What's his deal?

326
00:19:26,667 --> 00:19:28,475
Understood.

327
00:19:29,856 --> 00:19:31,398
Looks like he's actually flying solo.

328
00:19:31,398 --> 00:19:34,125
- Oh, come on, there's no way.
- He's by himself.

329
00:19:34,125 --> 00:19:37,083
His girlfriend's probably waiting
for him over there.

330
00:19:37,083 --> 00:19:40,583
Oh, that's the deal?

331
00:19:40,583 --> 00:19:41,833
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

332
00:19:41,833 --> 00:19:44,875
<i>we're ready for takeoff.</i>

333
00:19:44,875 --> 00:19:46,625
<i>Please check</i>

334
00:19:46,625 --> 00:19:49,731
<i>that your seatbelts are fastened.</i>

335
00:19:49,731 --> 00:19:54,183
<i>Yumi stepped in
before Soon Rok's rule could crumble.</i>

336
00:19:56,167 --> 00:19:57,808
<i>But...</i>

337
00:20:01,708 --> 00:20:04,500
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, welcome to Osaka,</i>

338
00:20:04,500 --> 00:20:06,792
<i>a city beautiful in every season.</i>

339
00:20:06,792 --> 00:20:08,750
<i>The local time is...</i>

340
00:20:08,750 --> 00:20:10,833
<i>Noona, where are you?</i>

341
00:20:10,833 --> 00:20:12,975
<i>I just landed.</i>

342
00:20:18,731 --> 00:20:20,440
- Noona.
<i>- Soon Rok.</i>

343
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:22,792
<i>- I don't think I'm making it.</i>
- What?

344
00:20:22,792 --> 00:20:24,583
There are no tickets left.

345
00:20:24,583 --> 00:20:26,562
I can't believe it. There are so many flights

346
00:20:26,562 --> 00:20:28,148
and not a single seat open.

347
00:20:28,148 --> 00:20:30,583
<i>Everything's sold out through tomorrow morning.</i>

348
00:20:30,583 --> 00:20:34,542
So I'm heading back home.

349
00:20:34,542 --> 00:20:36,500
It's the weekend. That's why.

350
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:40,042
That's exactly why you should've
just gotten on the earlier flight.

351
00:20:40,042 --> 00:20:41,292
It's only a one-night trip.

352
00:20:41,292 --> 00:20:43,833
Taking an afternoon flight tomorrow
doesn't make any sense.

353
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:45,708
<i>Right?</i>

354
00:20:45,708 --> 00:20:47,083
It is what it is.

355
00:20:47,083 --> 00:20:50,042
You're already there, so at least enjoy it.
Get some rest, okay?

356
00:20:50,042 --> 00:20:52,475
- No, it's just...
- PD Shin.

357
00:20:57,083 --> 00:20:59,142
Don't tell me you got stood up.

358
00:20:59,917 --> 00:21:01,725
That's not it, right?

359
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:05,375
Your girlfriend's waiting at the airport?

360
00:21:05,375 --> 00:21:07,917
You didn't actually come all the way here
by yourself, did you?

361
00:21:07,917 --> 00:21:10,125
Oh, come on, of course not.

362
00:21:10,125 --> 00:21:12,917
He's in a different league from us.

363
00:21:12,917 --> 00:21:15,183
Oh, please.

364
00:21:16,292 --> 00:21:17,667
Take care.

365
00:21:17,667 --> 00:21:20,106
- Call me.
- Let's get moving.

366
00:21:20,106 --> 00:21:21,417
I'm so stiff.

367
00:21:21,417 --> 00:21:24,831
My body just isn't what it used to be.

368
00:23:17,875 --> 00:23:21,375
<i>Thank you for flying with us.</i>

369
00:23:21,375 --> 00:23:25,042
<i>We've arrived at our destination.</i>

370
00:23:25,042 --> 00:23:26,792
<i>Please remain seated</i>

371
00:23:26,792 --> 00:23:29,000
<i>until the aircraft has come to a complete stop</i>

372
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:31,750
<i>and the seatbelt sign has been turned off.</i>

373
00:23:31,750 --> 00:23:34,167
<i>Soon Rok, call me when you land.</i>

374
00:23:34,167 --> 00:23:36,308
<i>I came out to pick you up.</i>

375
00:23:43,708 --> 00:23:45,392
Soon Rok!

376
00:23:56,917 --> 00:23:58,125
I could've just taken the bus.

377
00:23:58,125 --> 00:24:00,558
I still came. I couldn't wait to see you.

378
00:24:01,667 --> 00:24:02,875
Let me take the wheel.

379
00:24:02,875 --> 00:24:04,375
You sure?

380
00:24:04,375 --> 00:24:05,750
A gift.

381
00:24:05,750 --> 00:24:08,292
What's this? Oh! Let's go!

382
00:24:08,292 --> 00:24:10,267
We'll have it with beer.

383
00:24:13,583 --> 00:24:15,625
Of all the flights at that time,

384
00:24:15,625 --> 00:24:18,875
how did they end up on the exact same one?

385
00:24:18,875 --> 00:24:21,000
The timing just could not have been worse.

386
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:23,558
I really wanted to see Kyoto.

387
00:24:29,458 --> 00:24:31,208
What did you end up doing there?

388
00:24:31,208 --> 00:24:33,583
Took a bath, had a meal, slept.

389
00:24:33,583 --> 00:24:37,558
Woke up, ate, took another bath, and came back.

390
00:24:39,042 --> 00:24:40,333
Sounds like a solid rest.

391
00:24:40,333 --> 00:24:42,683
Yeah, it really was.

392
00:24:46,256 --> 00:24:47,975
Are you upset?

393
00:24:48,750 --> 00:24:49,750
Not at all.

394
00:24:49,750 --> 00:24:51,292
Then how come you seem like you are?

395
00:24:51,292 --> 00:24:54,350
There's nothing for me
to be upset at you about.

396
00:24:56,667 --> 00:24:59,292
I was so frustrated too.

397
00:24:59,292 --> 00:25:04,042
Can you imagine how I felt?
I turned around right at the gate.

398
00:25:04,042 --> 00:25:07,333
But I did it because I didn't
want to put you in a difficult spot.

399
00:25:07,333 --> 00:25:10,833
You're the one who kept hammering
on keeping work and personal stuff separate,

400
00:25:10,833 --> 00:25:13,333
so what if we just get busted out
in the open like that?

401
00:25:13,333 --> 00:25:15,767
You have a reputation to protect.

402
00:25:17,333 --> 00:25:19,856
That stupid rule.

403
00:25:19,856 --> 00:25:21,517
What?

404
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:28,267
Where are we going?

405
00:25:53,542 --> 00:25:55,375
Who are you calling?

406
00:25:55,375 --> 00:25:57,356
[PD Shin Soon Rok]

407
00:25:57,356 --> 00:25:59,583
- Hello?
<i>- Hey.</i>

408
00:25:59,583 --> 00:26:02,208
<i>It's Soon Rok.</i>

409
00:26:02,208 --> 00:26:03,792
There's something I need to tell you.

410
00:26:03,792 --> 00:26:05,917
<i>Yeah, what's up?</i>

411
00:26:05,917 --> 00:26:07,625
So...

412
00:26:07,625 --> 00:26:10,225
Writer Kim Yumi and I are together.

413
00:26:13,648 --> 00:26:15,625
Wait, what?

414
00:26:15,625 --> 00:26:18,000
[PD Shin Soon Rok]
<i>Writer Kim Yumi and I are in a relationship.</i>

415
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:19,808
<i>It's been a little while now.</i>

416
00:26:21,981 --> 00:26:23,231
What...

417
00:26:23,231 --> 00:26:24,583
What did you just say?

418
00:26:24,583 --> 00:26:26,440
<i>So now you know.</i>

419
00:26:26,440 --> 00:26:29,542
<i>I'll fill you in on the rest later.</i>

420
00:26:29,542 --> 00:26:31,417
<i>Enjoy the rest of your trip.</i>

421
00:26:31,417 --> 00:26:34,017
Hello...

422
00:26:41,250 --> 00:26:45,099
[The Golden Rule:
No office dating, no getting caught]

423
00:27:22,565 --> 00:27:23,731
Noona.

424
00:27:23,731 --> 00:27:25,708
We can finally take a trip whenever we want.

425
00:27:25,708 --> 00:27:27,375
Hey, what are you thinking? Your rule...

426
00:27:27,375 --> 00:27:29,210
That stupid rule
and everything that came with it.

427
00:27:29,210 --> 00:27:30,917
I'm done with all of it.

428
00:27:30,917 --> 00:27:32,690
What's the point of having rules?

429
00:27:32,690 --> 00:27:34,725
They all break eventually anyway.

430
00:27:36,731 --> 00:27:38,667
Because of me?

431
00:27:38,667 --> 00:27:43,190
All of your rules are crumbling because of me?

432
00:27:43,190 --> 00:27:45,725
Because you like me that much?

433
00:27:47,356 --> 00:27:49,933
Could you maybe dial back the ego a little?

434
00:27:51,583 --> 00:27:53,833
Oh no.

435
00:27:53,833 --> 00:27:57,308
All those precious rules of yours,
gone because of me.

436
00:27:58,208 --> 00:28:01,167
That was never my intention.

437
00:28:01,167 --> 00:28:04,100
I was actually trying
to protect your precious rules...

438
00:28:13,667 --> 00:28:15,167
But, Soon Rok.

439
00:28:15,167 --> 00:28:17,292
Honestly? I feel incredible right now.

440
00:28:17,292 --> 00:28:19,500
The birthday gift, the Kyoto trip.

441
00:28:19,500 --> 00:28:22,083
None of that comes close
to how I feel right now.

442
00:28:22,083 --> 00:28:23,975
Same here.

443
00:28:48,333 --> 00:28:52,583
<i>And just like that, the Tower of Principles
in Soon Rok's village came down.</i>

444
00:28:52,583 --> 00:28:55,142
<i>Claimed by Noona Yumi.</i>

445
00:28:55,958 --> 00:28:59,417
<i>All that's left now is the rubble.</i>

446
00:28:59,417 --> 00:29:04,167
<i>Conquered by Noona Yumi.
On Noona Yumi's birthday.</i>

447
00:29:06,083 --> 00:29:09,005
[Episode 23: One Track Life]

448
00:29:11,375 --> 00:29:13,058
Morning.

449
00:29:14,440 --> 00:29:16,350
Hey there.

450
00:29:17,898 --> 00:29:19,767
Hello.

451
00:29:23,981 --> 00:29:25,940
Oh, PD Shin, you're in.

452
00:29:25,940 --> 00:29:27,125
Yeah.

453
00:29:27,125 --> 00:29:29,481
The editor's been asking for you.
For a while now.

454
00:29:29,481 --> 00:29:31,731
He told me to let him know
the moment you showed up.

455
00:29:31,731 --> 00:29:33,875
Give me a second.
I need to send something out first.

456
00:29:33,875 --> 00:29:36,933
Soon Rok, in my office.

457
00:29:39,921 --> 00:29:41,933
What did you do?

458
00:29:43,167 --> 00:29:44,792
Not sure.

459
00:30:01,292 --> 00:30:02,667
How was the golf?

460
00:30:02,667 --> 00:30:06,333
How I played has nothing to do with you.

461
00:30:06,333 --> 00:30:08,417
Hey, you little...

462
00:30:08,417 --> 00:30:10,917
PDs who can't separate work
from their personal lives.

463
00:30:10,917 --> 00:30:13,000
PDs who date their own writers.

464
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:14,917
You said they should all be cut, right?

465
00:30:14,917 --> 00:30:16,833
You called them people
with zero professional sense.

466
00:30:16,833 --> 00:30:19,113
Your words, not mine.

467
00:30:21,042 --> 00:30:22,375
I remember every word of it.

468
00:30:22,375 --> 00:30:23,509
You said flirting would
never even be on your radar.

469
00:30:23,509 --> 00:30:25,898
That was your rule, wasn't it?

470
00:30:25,898 --> 00:30:27,583
- It was.
- And?

471
00:30:27,583 --> 00:30:29,792
I mean,

472
00:30:29,792 --> 00:30:32,292
isn't it possible

473
00:30:32,292 --> 00:30:34,815
for a person's rules to shift over time?

474
00:30:34,815 --> 00:30:36,208
Come again?

475
00:30:36,208 --> 00:30:39,725
People's thinking changes.

476
00:30:42,898 --> 00:30:44,625
How is this guy so shameless?

477
00:30:44,625 --> 00:30:47,417
Change is what makes us human.
Otherwise, we'd just be robots, right?

478
00:30:47,417 --> 00:30:49,433
Oh, look at this guy.

479
00:30:50,856 --> 00:30:52,292
You're laughing? Hey.

480
00:30:52,292 --> 00:30:54,292
What exactly do you have to smile about?

481
00:30:54,292 --> 00:30:55,962
Sorry, but there's a message
I need to send right away.

482
00:30:55,962 --> 00:30:57,398
Would it be alright if I handled that first?

483
00:30:57,398 --> 00:30:58,875
You're trying to slip out on me, aren't you?

484
00:30:58,875 --> 00:31:00,763
There's a reschedule request
for tomorrow's meeting.

485
00:31:00,763 --> 00:31:02,148
- From Shanghai.
- Oh, Shanghai?

486
00:31:02,148 --> 00:31:03,208
Oh, well, Shanghai's non-negotiable.

487
00:31:03,208 --> 00:31:05,167
Fine, let's talk over lunch then.

488
00:31:05,167 --> 00:31:06,792
Lunch doesn't work for me.

489
00:31:06,792 --> 00:31:07,958
And why not?

490
00:31:07,958 --> 00:31:10,167
What makes you so special
that you can't even make time for lunch?

491
00:31:10,167 --> 00:31:11,500
I have somewhere I need to be.

492
00:31:11,500 --> 00:31:14,083
Let me guess. Another date?

493
00:31:14,083 --> 00:31:15,917
Not exactly.

494
00:31:15,917 --> 00:31:18,792
I never got to give the birthday gift.

495
00:31:18,792 --> 00:31:21,083
I'm heading on a work trip today,

496
00:31:21,083 --> 00:31:23,523
and I won't see her for another week.

497
00:31:23,523 --> 00:31:26,273
Just out in the open like this?

498
00:31:26,273 --> 00:31:27,398
Man...

499
00:31:27,398 --> 00:31:29,600
You weren't like this before.

500
00:31:31,023 --> 00:31:33,315
I've always been this way.

501
00:31:33,315 --> 00:31:36,725
The direction's just different now.

502
00:31:39,690 --> 00:31:43,142
<i>The Tower of Principles had long stood
as the heart of Soon Rok's village.</i>

503
00:31:44,356 --> 00:31:49,433
<i>A warrior known as the Straight-Path General
had spent his life defending it.</i>

504
00:31:52,083 --> 00:31:54,017
Watch out!

505
00:31:54,898 --> 00:31:58,600
<i>After 29 years of standing guard,
the tower finally fell.</i>

506
00:31:59,542 --> 00:32:03,267
<i>With nothing left to protect,
the Straight-Path General was lost.</i>

507
00:32:03,940 --> 00:32:07,440
What's left for me to guard now?

508
00:32:07,440 --> 00:32:10,958
<i>Without something worth dedicating
his whole life to protecting,</i>

509
00:32:10,958 --> 00:32:14,225
<i>there was no reason for this cell to exist.</i>

510
00:32:18,940 --> 00:32:22,142
<i>He finally made his choice.</i>

511
00:32:28,708 --> 00:32:31,641
<i>The one who had brought the tower down,
the conqueror who came through love.</i>

512
00:32:35,356 --> 00:32:38,725
<i>He swore to spend the rest of his days
protecting Noona Yumi.</i>

513
00:32:47,273 --> 00:32:49,225
Welcome in.

514
00:32:50,273 --> 00:32:53,083
Is there something specific
I can help you find?

515
00:32:53,083 --> 00:32:54,817
I'd like to look at some earrings for a woman.

516
00:32:54,817 --> 00:32:57,183
Of course, right this way.

517
00:32:58,875 --> 00:33:01,606
Is there a particular style you have in mind?

518
00:33:01,606 --> 00:33:02,898
Not really.

519
00:33:02,898 --> 00:33:04,148
It's a birthday present.

520
00:33:04,148 --> 00:33:05,773
For your girlfriend?

521
00:33:05,773 --> 00:33:06,815
That's right.

522
00:33:06,815 --> 00:33:09,415
What are her tastes like?

523
00:33:10,292 --> 00:33:12,975
That I'm not too sure about.

524
00:33:13,815 --> 00:33:15,917
But I know she's not into anything too big.

525
00:33:15,917 --> 00:33:17,292
Not into big pieces?

526
00:33:17,292 --> 00:33:19,148
She has a really small face.

527
00:33:19,148 --> 00:33:21,667
Something oversized just wouldn't suit her.

528
00:33:21,667 --> 00:33:25,058
Oh, I see, so she has a petite face?

529
00:33:25,773 --> 00:33:29,023
It's literally fist-sized.

530
00:33:29,023 --> 00:33:31,183
And her skin is so fair...

531
00:33:32,208 --> 00:33:33,398
Yeah.

532
00:33:33,398 --> 00:33:35,458
Very small face, very fair skin.

533
00:33:35,458 --> 00:33:37,475
Got it.

534
00:33:38,273 --> 00:33:40,167
Would more details be helpful?

535
00:33:40,167 --> 00:33:41,542
Oh, yes.

536
00:33:41,542 --> 00:33:44,433
It definitely makes it easier for me
to point you in the right direction.

537
00:33:46,315 --> 00:33:48,667
She's on the intellectual side.

538
00:33:48,667 --> 00:33:50,708
Elegant, too.

539
00:33:50,708 --> 00:33:52,475
And...

540
00:33:53,625 --> 00:33:55,273
Her smile is something else.

541
00:33:55,273 --> 00:33:56,589
She's slender.

542
00:33:56,589 --> 00:34:00,083
Actually, more like delicate.

543
00:34:00,083 --> 00:34:02,440
The kind of person you just want to look after.

544
00:34:02,440 --> 00:34:05,231
You know what I mean?

545
00:34:05,231 --> 00:34:07,350
Oh, sure.

546
00:34:10,190 --> 00:34:12,458
Do you have anything
that would work for someone like that?

547
00:34:12,458 --> 00:34:16,208
So this section here
has been really popular lately.

548
00:34:16,208 --> 00:34:19,625
For someone intellectual and elegant
with a small face,

549
00:34:19,625 --> 00:34:23,375
something understated would probably
work better than anything flashy.

550
00:34:23,375 --> 00:34:25,017
Right.

551
00:34:40,981 --> 00:34:42,565
Straight-Path General!

552
00:34:42,565 --> 00:34:44,125
Come back!

553
00:34:44,125 --> 00:34:45,899
- That's not the village!
<i>- Soon Rok's Straight-Path General Cell</i>

554
00:34:45,899 --> 00:34:48,683
<i>had started walking a brand new path.</i>

555
00:34:50,148 --> 00:34:52,500
Straight-Path General.

556
00:34:52,500 --> 00:34:54,106
I'm not turning back.

557
00:34:54,106 --> 00:34:57,850
I've already committed to this road.

558
00:35:09,106 --> 00:35:11,767
Would you like to see something else?

559
00:35:13,750 --> 00:35:17,125
Could I get a closer look at that one?

560
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:32,333
Noona.

561
00:35:37,231 --> 00:35:39,190
It's hot out here. You could've waited inside.

562
00:35:39,190 --> 00:35:42,792
The weather's so nice
I actually chose to stay out here.

563
00:35:42,792 --> 00:35:44,767
But where are you coming from over there?

564
00:35:46,042 --> 00:35:47,291
Just browsing around.

565
00:35:48,542 --> 00:35:50,691
The editor was in today, right?

566
00:35:50,691 --> 00:35:52,625
Anything happen?

567
00:35:52,625 --> 00:35:54,667
I got interrogated for over an hour.

568
00:35:54,667 --> 00:35:55,958
A whole hour?

569
00:35:55,958 --> 00:35:58,750
Who gets grilled for that long?

570
00:35:58,750 --> 00:35:59,958
I'll fill you in on the way.

571
00:35:59,958 --> 00:36:02,708
I need to be at the airport by nine.

572
00:36:02,708 --> 00:36:05,398
Oh no, so we're short on time.

573
00:36:05,398 --> 00:36:07,458
Let's get food first. Come on.

574
00:36:07,458 --> 00:36:09,042
There are so many good places around here.

575
00:36:09,042 --> 00:36:11,000
Hold on, not around here.

576
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:13,458
There's a great spot in this neighborhood.
Let's go there.

577
00:36:13,458 --> 00:36:15,356
- A good spot?
- It's close by.

578
00:36:15,356 --> 00:36:16,975
Come on.

579
00:36:18,898 --> 00:36:20,667
There are plenty of good options
right here though.

580
00:36:20,667 --> 00:36:22,475
Trust me, that place is just as good.

581
00:36:28,481 --> 00:36:32,208
It's my go-to
every time I'm in this neighborhood.

582
00:36:32,208 --> 00:36:34,458
Pretty sure you'll love it.

583
00:36:34,458 --> 00:36:35,792
What kind of place is it?

584
00:36:35,792 --> 00:36:37,375
A bunsik place.

585
00:36:37,375 --> 00:36:39,375
It's been around for thirty years.

586
00:36:39,375 --> 00:36:41,169
Their tteokbokki is out of this world.

587
00:36:41,169 --> 00:36:43,892
Oh, I'm always down for tteokbokki.

588
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:46,565
Hold on a second.

589
00:36:46,565 --> 00:36:48,208
Something feels off...

590
00:36:48,208 --> 00:36:49,815
Right.

591
00:36:49,815 --> 00:36:53,642
Definitely... this alley...

592
00:36:55,981 --> 00:36:59,292
What's the place called?

593
00:36:59,292 --> 00:37:00,958
The name?

594
00:37:00,958 --> 00:37:02,808
It's...

595
00:37:03,958 --> 00:37:06,417
It's on the tip of my tongue.

596
00:37:06,417 --> 00:37:08,023
It's an English name.

597
00:37:08,023 --> 00:37:09,625
An English name?

598
00:37:09,625 --> 00:37:10,898
<i>Just a second.</i>

599
00:37:10,898 --> 00:37:13,167
<i>Please tell me
that's not the place we're heading to.</i>

600
00:37:13,167 --> 00:37:14,850
Over here.

601
00:37:18,875 --> 00:37:20,725
We're here.

602
00:37:22,648 --> 00:37:24,292
<i>It is that place!</i>

603
00:37:24,292 --> 00:37:27,625
Oh, right, yeah. Babi Bunsik.

604
00:37:27,625 --> 00:37:30,208
I come here all the time.
How did I blank on the name?

605
00:37:30,208 --> 00:37:32,699
This is your regular spot?

606
00:37:32,699 --> 00:37:33,875
Yeah.

607
00:37:33,875 --> 00:37:36,417
One bite and you'll see why.

608
00:37:36,417 --> 00:37:38,100
Let's go in.

609
00:37:42,292 --> 00:37:43,660
Let's find somewhere else.

610
00:37:43,660 --> 00:37:46,106
Why? I thought you were into tteokbokki.

611
00:37:46,106 --> 00:37:47,356
I am.

612
00:37:47,356 --> 00:37:48,981
It's just...

613
00:37:48,981 --> 00:37:50,958
I'm actually pretty full already.

614
00:37:50,958 --> 00:37:52,542
Or you could go in without me.

615
00:37:52,542 --> 00:37:55,042
I'll be over at that coffee shop waiting.

616
00:37:55,042 --> 00:37:56,523
What are you talking about?

617
00:37:56,523 --> 00:37:59,792
You have to try it no matter what. Full or not.

618
00:37:59,792 --> 00:38:00,792
Come on, let's just go.

619
00:38:00,792 --> 00:38:02,792
Oh, wait, I really...

620
00:38:02,792 --> 00:38:04,230
Hold on.

621
00:38:16,875 --> 00:38:18,792
[Babi Bunsik]

622
00:38:18,792 --> 00:38:21,725
[Closed for vacation: 07.24-07.31]

623
00:38:24,500 --> 00:38:26,892
They're on vacation.

624
00:38:28,500 --> 00:38:32,100
Let's go somewhere else.
I know another great tteokbokki place.

625
00:38:40,792 --> 00:38:43,500
Honestly, thank goodness they're closed.

626
00:38:43,500 --> 00:38:46,850
Running into Babi's dad
would've been so awkward.

627
00:38:52,458 --> 00:38:55,375
Hungry Cell, isn't this right up your alley?

628
00:38:55,375 --> 00:38:58,750
I lost my appetite
because I was so shocked back there.

629
00:38:58,750 --> 00:39:01,268
What's that thing on your head?

630
00:39:02,606 --> 00:39:06,225
Once things calm down,
the appetite comes back on its own.

631
00:39:14,708 --> 00:39:16,542
- This place is really good too.
- Right?

632
00:39:16,542 --> 00:39:17,917
It actually has quite a following.

633
00:39:17,917 --> 00:39:19,500
I should grab some to take home on the way out.

634
00:39:19,500 --> 00:39:22,683
They don't do takeout here though.

635
00:39:25,458 --> 00:39:27,869
Babi Bunsik does takeout though.

636
00:39:32,333 --> 00:39:33,958
This place is good, don't get me wrong.

637
00:39:33,958 --> 00:39:35,625
But it doesn't hold a candle to Babi Bunsik.

638
00:39:35,625 --> 00:39:40,017
The green onions and the broth together
are just on another level.

639
00:39:43,250 --> 00:39:45,875
I had no idea you were this serious

640
00:39:45,875 --> 00:39:48,767
about tteokbokki.

641
00:39:51,625 --> 00:39:53,958
Oh, but...

642
00:39:53,958 --> 00:39:55,975
What was that about earlier?

643
00:39:57,917 --> 00:39:59,792
Back at Babi Bunsik.

644
00:39:59,792 --> 00:40:02,933
How come you were so set on not going in?

645
00:40:08,333 --> 00:40:10,625
It's a whole thing.

646
00:40:10,625 --> 00:40:12,350
Like what?

647
00:40:15,125 --> 00:40:16,792
What do we do?

648
00:40:16,792 --> 00:40:18,875
Soon Rok picked up on it.

649
00:40:18,875 --> 00:40:20,083
Just tell him.

650
00:40:20,083 --> 00:40:22,667
Soon Rok is Yumi's boyfriend now.

651
00:40:22,667 --> 00:40:24,933
There shouldn't be any secrets between them.

652
00:40:26,978 --> 00:40:29,250
The thing is...

653
00:40:29,250 --> 00:40:30,933
that place...

654
00:40:31,940 --> 00:40:34,917
it's run by my ex's dad.

655
00:40:34,917 --> 00:40:36,875
I've actually been there before.

656
00:40:36,875 --> 00:40:38,773
So going back there is just...

657
00:40:38,773 --> 00:40:40,534
a little weird for me.

658
00:40:45,000 --> 00:40:46,808
Wait a minute.

659
00:40:52,440 --> 00:40:54,892
So your ex's name...

660
00:40:55,667 --> 00:40:58,106
is Babi?

661
00:40:58,106 --> 00:40:59,731
Is that right?

662
00:40:59,731 --> 00:41:01,850
That's right.

663
00:41:02,500 --> 00:41:05,375
Yeah, that makes sense.

664
00:41:05,375 --> 00:41:07,750
The owner named the place

665
00:41:07,750 --> 00:41:10,808
after his son. That's what he told me.

666
00:41:11,667 --> 00:41:14,767
So Babi it is.

667
00:41:17,250 --> 00:41:19,125
Oh, okay.

668
00:41:19,125 --> 00:41:21,125
Wait, though.

669
00:41:21,125 --> 00:41:23,042
I actually know that guy.

670
00:41:23,042 --> 00:41:24,250
You know him?

671
00:41:24,250 --> 00:41:25,250
Yeah.

672
00:41:25,250 --> 00:41:28,000
I've run into him at the counter a few times.

673
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:29,750
But, honestly,

674
00:41:29,750 --> 00:41:31,517
that guy...

675
00:41:32,625 --> 00:41:35,267
was seriously good-looking.

676
00:41:35,856 --> 00:41:37,583
- Not really.
- No, for real.

677
00:41:37,583 --> 00:41:39,583
He was really good-looking.

678
00:41:39,583 --> 00:41:41,892
That's literally why I remember him.

679
00:41:44,417 --> 00:41:48,058
Oh no, Soon Rok's bothered by it.

680
00:41:49,167 --> 00:41:51,975
It's like he's overthinking it too much.

681
00:41:53,375 --> 00:41:55,333
He was just...

682
00:41:55,333 --> 00:41:57,458
totally average.

683
00:41:57,458 --> 00:41:58,875
Very ordinary...

684
00:41:58,875 --> 00:42:00,725
Come on...

685
00:42:06,208 --> 00:42:08,225
So you do care about looks.

686
00:42:18,417 --> 00:42:20,292
Oh, absolutely.

687
00:42:20,292 --> 00:42:22,125
Looks matter to me.

688
00:42:22,125 --> 00:42:25,148
Thanks for being so handsome.

689
00:42:25,148 --> 00:42:27,350
Credit goes to my parents.

690
00:42:29,315 --> 00:42:32,833
I'm so glad he's this relaxed about it.

691
00:42:32,833 --> 00:42:35,683
Not sure if it's confidence
or just pure obliviousness, but still.

692
00:42:37,250 --> 00:42:41,017
Oh good. My appetite's back.

693
00:42:45,606 --> 00:42:47,458
Straight-Path General!

694
00:42:47,458 --> 00:42:50,333
Stop just pushing forward for a second.

695
00:42:50,333 --> 00:42:52,975
We're talking about Yumi's ex here.

696
00:42:54,231 --> 00:42:56,667
Could that be the person we heard about before?

697
00:42:56,667 --> 00:43:00,231
The one she broke up with
because he fell for a younger intern.

698
00:43:00,231 --> 00:43:01,875
What does it matter?

699
00:43:01,875 --> 00:43:04,667
I've already picked this path.

700
00:43:04,667 --> 00:43:06,500
Still though.

701
00:43:06,500 --> 00:43:09,125
Aren't you the least bit curious?

702
00:43:09,125 --> 00:43:10,933
Step aside.

703
00:43:13,542 --> 00:43:16,058
<i>One track. That's the only life he knows.</i>

704
00:43:21,273 --> 00:43:22,975
What?

705
00:43:24,125 --> 00:43:27,042
<i>The Straight-Path General
kept moving without stopping</i>

706
00:43:27,042 --> 00:43:30,000
<i>until he finally reached where he was headed.</i>

707
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:32,333
Who is he?
Is he a cell from Soon Rok's village?

708
00:43:32,333 --> 00:43:34,690
It's not Love Cell though.

709
00:43:34,690 --> 00:43:36,600
- Who are you?
- Who are you?

710
00:43:43,000 --> 00:43:44,000
- What's going on?
- What's going on?

711
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:46,058
I said, who are you?

712
00:43:49,792 --> 00:43:52,600
A face the size of a fist!

713
00:43:54,167 --> 00:43:57,017
Skin as white as snow!

714
00:43:59,042 --> 00:44:00,481
What?

715
00:44:00,481 --> 00:44:02,250
A face the size of a fist!

716
00:44:02,250 --> 00:44:05,208
Blessed with skin as pale as fresh snow,

717
00:44:05,208 --> 00:44:09,625
born with both brilliance and grace!

718
00:44:09,625 --> 00:44:13,125
Whose smile is worth a million dollars,

719
00:44:13,125 --> 00:44:17,267
so delicate all you want to do
is keep her safe!

720
00:44:21,583 --> 00:44:23,625
Conqueror,

721
00:44:23,625 --> 00:44:26,017
Kim Yumi!

722
00:44:30,333 --> 00:44:32,583
I've come from Soon Rok's village.

723
00:44:32,583 --> 00:44:36,023
Guardian of Soon Rok's village.
The Straight-Path General.

724
00:44:36,023 --> 00:44:39,125
Please open these gates wide and clear the way,

725
00:44:39,125 --> 00:44:42,167
so that I may spend my whole life
walking a single path for you

726
00:44:42,167 --> 00:44:45,476
and keeping you safe.

727
00:44:46,833 --> 00:44:48,500
Straight-Path General Cell?

728
00:44:48,500 --> 00:44:50,542
We don't have anything
like that in our village.

729
00:44:50,542 --> 00:44:52,667
Must be something that only exists
in Soon Rok's village.

730
00:44:52,667 --> 00:44:54,083
He says he'll protect her.

731
00:44:54,083 --> 00:44:56,517
What exactly is he planning to do?

732
00:45:07,190 --> 00:45:08,850
Pretty good, right?

733
00:45:11,083 --> 00:45:12,892
Really good.

734
00:45:15,023 --> 00:45:16,458
I'm telling you, tteokbokki first

735
00:45:16,458 --> 00:45:19,292
and then this place's einspanner.
That's the perfect combo.

736
00:45:19,292 --> 00:45:21,583
I was actually the one
who discovered this place last year.

737
00:45:21,583 --> 00:45:23,458
Back then, nobody had heard of it.

738
00:45:23,458 --> 00:45:28,225
Then six months later it just blew up.

739
00:45:32,833 --> 00:45:34,125
What's this?

740
00:45:34,125 --> 00:45:35,981
Your birthday present.

741
00:45:35,981 --> 00:45:37,042
Wait, really?

742
00:45:37,042 --> 00:45:39,398
You already gave me one.

743
00:45:39,398 --> 00:45:41,167
You covered the whole trip.

744
00:45:41,167 --> 00:45:44,267
That doesn't count. I ended up going alone.

745
00:45:45,250 --> 00:45:47,042
I'm okay with it.

746
00:45:47,042 --> 00:45:48,626
Open it.

747
00:45:49,292 --> 00:45:53,292
I wasn't expecting this at all.

748
00:45:53,292 --> 00:45:55,542
But what is this?

749
00:45:55,542 --> 00:45:57,892
This is a really expensive brand.

750
00:45:58,625 --> 00:46:00,392
Is it a pair of earrings?

751
00:46:12,565 --> 00:46:13,917
It's a ring.

752
00:46:13,917 --> 00:46:14,917
Yeah.

753
00:46:14,917 --> 00:46:16,125
A ring?

754
00:46:16,125 --> 00:46:18,625
A ring for a birthday present?

755
00:46:18,625 --> 00:46:20,642
A ring though...

756
00:46:24,083 --> 00:46:26,750
Oh, it's beautiful.

757
00:46:26,750 --> 00:46:29,417
But this is crystal, right?

758
00:46:29,417 --> 00:46:31,183
It's real.

759
00:46:32,042 --> 00:46:35,225
- It's real?
- Of course it is.

760
00:46:37,232 --> 00:46:40,458
You're saying this is actually a diamond ring?

761
00:46:40,458 --> 00:46:43,417
You're giving me
a diamond ring for my birthday?

762
00:46:43,417 --> 00:46:45,417
Try it on.
We'll need to exchange it if it doesn't fit.

763
00:46:45,417 --> 00:46:47,625
Oh, hold on, this...

764
00:46:47,625 --> 00:46:48,958
How much did this cost?

765
00:46:48,958 --> 00:46:50,792
Just looking at it...

766
00:46:52,417 --> 00:46:55,069
Who gives something like this
as a birthday gift?

767
00:46:55,069 --> 00:46:56,292
This is way too much.

768
00:46:56,292 --> 00:46:57,324
Why not?

769
00:46:57,324 --> 00:46:58,981
It's perfectly fine.

770
00:46:58,981 --> 00:47:00,750
It's beautiful.

771
00:47:00,750 --> 00:47:02,333
So every time something's pretty
you just buy it?

772
00:47:02,333 --> 00:47:06,042
Is your family a conglomerate or something?
Because they're not.

773
00:47:06,042 --> 00:47:09,000
I don't even know what to do
with this right now.

774
00:47:09,000 --> 00:47:11,208
Does spending like this not even faze you?

775
00:47:11,208 --> 00:47:13,042
I just thought
it would look really good on you.

776
00:47:13,042 --> 00:47:15,167
That's not a reason to just go out and buy it.

777
00:47:15,167 --> 00:47:16,875
I didn't just pick it up on a whim.

778
00:47:16,875 --> 00:47:18,933
I thought of it as a birthday gift...

779
00:47:19,667 --> 00:47:22,523
and a proposal ring at the same time.

780
00:47:22,523 --> 00:47:23,958
A proposal?

781
00:47:23,958 --> 00:47:25,808
A proposal?

782
00:47:27,625 --> 00:47:30,458
That just knocked my appetite right out again.

783
00:47:30,458 --> 00:47:33,642
- Did I hear that right?
- Now!

784
00:47:34,625 --> 00:47:36,792
Open the gates wide

785
00:47:36,792 --> 00:47:40,142
and let me in!

786
00:47:41,792 --> 00:47:43,875
A single path, just for you.

787
00:47:43,875 --> 00:47:46,517
I'll walk it for the rest of my life.

788
00:47:53,356 --> 00:47:55,058
Noona.

789
00:47:56,625 --> 00:47:58,308
What if we...

790
00:47:59,500 --> 00:48:01,683
got married?

791
00:48:03,875 --> 00:48:06,308
I think it'd be pretty great.

792
00:48:07,958 --> 00:48:10,100
What do you think?

793
00:48:37,208 --> 00:48:40,331
[Episode 24: The Third Proposal]

794
00:48:44,708 --> 00:48:48,308
What do you think?

795
00:49:01,331 --> 00:49:04,375
What's going on?

796
00:49:04,375 --> 00:49:06,625
Soon Rok just proposed!

797
00:49:06,625 --> 00:49:09,375
- A proposal?
- Right in the middle of einspanner?

798
00:49:09,375 --> 00:49:11,808
- Let's go see!
- Let's go!

799
00:49:12,708 --> 00:49:14,375
Let's go!

800
00:49:14,375 --> 00:49:16,083
Rational Cell, where are you headed?

801
00:49:16,083 --> 00:49:18,190
Didn't Yumi just get proposed to?

802
00:49:18,190 --> 00:49:20,975
There's something I need to check. Come on!

803
00:49:26,273 --> 00:49:31,606
<i>The unexpected proposal brought
the past flooding back after a long time.</i>

804
00:49:31,606 --> 00:49:33,417
A proposal. A proposal...

805
00:49:33,417 --> 00:49:35,434
Here it is!

806
00:49:40,375 --> 00:49:44,417
<i>There had been two proposals in Yumi's life.</i>

807
00:49:44,417 --> 00:49:46,083
<i>The first one...</i>

808
00:49:46,083 --> 00:49:47,850
<i>Hey, Ung.</i>

809
00:49:48,500 --> 00:49:50,417
<i>Should we...</i>

810
00:49:50,417 --> 00:49:52,308
<i>get married?</i>

811
00:49:54,167 --> 00:49:56,517
<i>Yumi was the one who asked,</i>

812
00:49:58,375 --> 00:50:00,600
<i>but she never got an answer.</i>

813
00:50:01,241 --> 00:50:02,500
<i>Got it.</i>

814
00:50:02,500 --> 00:50:03,750
<i>I haven't said anything yet.</i>

815
00:50:03,750 --> 00:50:04,792
<i>I was just...</i>

816
00:50:04,792 --> 00:50:08,500
<i>curious what you were thinking. That's all.</i>

817
00:50:08,500 --> 00:50:10,917
<i>You don't need to stress about it.</i>

818
00:50:10,917 --> 00:50:13,333
<i>The second proposal...</i>

819
00:50:13,333 --> 00:50:15,142
<i>Yumi.</i>

820
00:50:16,500 --> 00:50:19,683
<i>Let's get married.</i>

821
00:50:22,083 --> 00:50:24,417
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

822
00:50:24,417 --> 00:50:26,767
<i>I think I know what you mean.</i>

823
00:50:30,083 --> 00:50:32,898
<i>Yumi handed back the ring
and that was the end of it.</i>

824
00:50:32,898 --> 00:50:34,523
When was all this again?

825
00:50:34,523 --> 00:50:37,833
With Ung, she proposed nine months in.

826
00:50:37,833 --> 00:50:40,625
With Babi, she received his proposal
at one year and four months.

827
00:50:40,625 --> 00:50:42,083
And now with Soon Rok?

828
00:50:42,083 --> 00:50:44,017
One month in.

829
00:50:45,981 --> 00:50:47,792
This is way too fast.

830
00:50:47,792 --> 00:50:49,725
This just isn't right!

831
00:50:52,667 --> 00:50:53,792
Hungry Cell!

832
00:50:53,792 --> 00:50:55,737
Give me a lift!

833
00:50:57,635 --> 00:51:00,083
What took you so long? I've been waiting.

834
00:51:00,083 --> 00:51:02,542
Let's just say yes already.

835
00:51:02,542 --> 00:51:04,042
No.

836
00:51:04,042 --> 00:51:05,042
How come?

837
00:51:05,042 --> 00:51:08,458
They checked all the boxes,
time, effort, everything,

838
00:51:08,458 --> 00:51:10,292
and yet, no happy ending.

839
00:51:10,292 --> 00:51:12,417
And now after just one month?

840
00:51:12,417 --> 00:51:13,750
This is being reckless.

841
00:51:13,750 --> 00:51:15,000
She needs to turn it down for now.

842
00:51:15,000 --> 00:51:18,042
If she misses this moment, what then?

843
00:51:18,042 --> 00:51:20,142
What if he takes it back?

844
00:51:20,917 --> 00:51:24,625
What if Soon Rok never works up
the nerve to propose again?

845
00:51:24,625 --> 00:51:27,667
Even so, she can't just rush
into an answer like this.

846
00:51:27,667 --> 00:51:29,417
Yumi isn't young anymore.

847
00:51:29,417 --> 00:51:31,606
Oh, give it a rest.

848
00:51:31,606 --> 00:51:34,708
- I'm stronger now, you know.
- Let go of me!

849
00:51:34,708 --> 00:51:40,183
We need to answer
before the einspanner goes completely flat.

850
00:51:44,667 --> 00:51:46,083
Noona,

851
00:51:46,083 --> 00:51:48,017
what do you think?

852
00:51:51,667 --> 00:51:53,167
Everyone, stop!

853
00:51:53,167 --> 00:51:56,417
Emotion Cell is right.
Love is all about timing.

854
00:51:56,417 --> 00:52:00,500
If Yumi loves Soon Rok,
there's no reason to hold back.

855
00:52:00,500 --> 00:52:01,708
But still...

856
00:52:01,708 --> 00:52:03,683
I'll be the one to decide.

857
00:52:04,333 --> 00:52:05,898
I'm Love Cell.

858
00:52:05,898 --> 00:52:09,392
In the name of the Prime Cell,
I'm accepting this proposal...

859
00:52:10,208 --> 00:52:11,458
Love Cell!

860
00:52:11,458 --> 00:52:13,226
- Love Cell!
- Love Cell!

861
00:52:14,958 --> 00:52:16,975
Who gave you the authority!

862
00:52:19,833 --> 00:52:21,875
I'm the Prime Cell!

863
00:52:21,875 --> 00:52:23,333
So am I!

864
00:52:23,333 --> 00:52:25,042
I'm the Prime Cell here!

865
00:52:25,042 --> 00:52:27,023
I, Writer Cell,

866
00:52:27,023 --> 00:52:28,958
in the name of the Prime Cell,

867
00:52:28,958 --> 00:52:31,017
am against this!

868
00:52:35,667 --> 00:52:36,917
Are you serious?

869
00:52:36,917 --> 00:52:38,880
The manuscript is already behind
because of this relationship.

870
00:52:38,880 --> 00:52:40,958
Do you have any idea?

871
00:52:40,958 --> 00:52:43,125
Why is marriage even on the table
while she's still mid-series?

872
00:52:43,125 --> 00:52:46,292
Tell him to come back
after everything's wrapped up!

873
00:52:46,292 --> 00:52:49,731
If he gets hurt over this,
are you taking responsibility?

874
00:52:49,731 --> 00:52:54,208
Any PD who gets hurt over a manuscript
has no business being a PD!

875
00:52:54,208 --> 00:52:55,792
Hey everyone,

876
00:52:55,792 --> 00:52:58,833
we probably need an answer soon.

877
00:52:58,833 --> 00:53:01,850
Too much time is passing.

878
00:53:11,125 --> 00:53:12,808
Noona?

879
00:53:14,000 --> 00:53:17,767
Is marrying me something
you've never even thought about?

880
00:53:28,231 --> 00:53:30,250
There's a call coming in. Isn't that work?

881
00:53:30,250 --> 00:53:31,933
Pick it up.

882
00:53:37,875 --> 00:53:39,375
Hello?

883
00:53:39,375 --> 00:53:41,417
Are you on your way?

884
00:53:41,417 --> 00:53:44,875
Yeah, I'm about to head out.

885
00:53:44,875 --> 00:53:46,892
I'll catch the airport bus.

886
00:53:47,500 --> 00:53:49,458
Let's meet at the counter.

887
00:53:49,458 --> 00:53:51,142
Sure thing.

888
00:53:53,148 --> 00:53:54,583
Everyone's already left?

889
00:53:54,583 --> 00:53:56,333
We're running late. Let's get up.

890
00:53:56,333 --> 00:53:59,792
- No, I'm not late yet...
- What if you miss the bus?

891
00:53:59,792 --> 00:54:02,058
- Let's move.
- No, listen...

892
00:54:11,750 --> 00:54:14,017
Oh, wait. Isn't that it?

893
00:54:15,000 --> 00:54:17,875
It'll fill up and you won't get on. Let's run.

894
00:54:17,875 --> 00:54:19,767
Soon Rok, hurry up.

895
00:54:24,708 --> 00:54:27,333
You'll make it in time, right?
Call me once you arrive.

896
00:54:27,333 --> 00:54:28,690
[Incheon International Airport]

897
00:54:28,690 --> 00:54:30,833
Oh, okay.

898
00:54:30,833 --> 00:54:32,792
- But...
- Take care of yourself.

899
00:54:32,792 --> 00:54:34,558
Get on, quick.

900
00:54:53,042 --> 00:54:56,017
We'll talk later.

901
00:55:40,917 --> 00:55:42,892
Let go of me!

902
00:55:59,375 --> 00:56:00,625
<i>The thing is,</i>

903
00:56:00,625 --> 00:56:03,975
<i>we never got Noona's answer.</i>

904
00:56:27,750 --> 00:56:31,600
Soon Rok's probably
not feeling great right now.

905
00:56:44,250 --> 00:56:46,875
Do you think Soon Rok is hurt?

906
00:56:46,875 --> 00:56:49,125
Pretty likely.

907
00:56:49,125 --> 00:56:51,542
Yumi's been through that kind of hurt before.

908
00:56:51,542 --> 00:56:53,208
When?

909
00:56:53,208 --> 00:56:56,542
When Ung didn't say anything back.

910
00:56:56,542 --> 00:57:01,333
I think I finally get why Ung couldn't respond.

911
00:57:01,333 --> 00:57:03,792
It wasn't that he didn't love Yumi.

912
00:57:03,792 --> 00:57:06,808
There was just too much weighing on him.

913
00:57:08,125 --> 00:57:11,250
Back then it felt like such a betrayal.

914
00:57:11,250 --> 00:57:14,375
But now it makes sense.

915
00:57:14,375 --> 00:57:15,750
Even so,

916
00:57:15,750 --> 00:57:19,208
overthinking it is exactly
what made him lose Yumi.

917
00:57:19,208 --> 00:57:21,792
Love has its window.

918
00:57:21,792 --> 00:57:24,350
Once it closes, it's hard to get back.

919
00:57:25,148 --> 00:57:27,183
That's not wrong.

920
00:57:37,875 --> 00:57:41,475
But what if she puts it on
and later has to take it back?

921
00:57:42,708 --> 00:57:47,625
Returning a ring after wearing it
leaves a wound that doesn't heal easily.

922
00:57:47,625 --> 00:57:50,917
That's actually worse
than never putting it on at all.

923
00:57:50,917 --> 00:57:53,183
Are we really going to put someone
through that again?

924
00:58:03,667 --> 00:58:05,583
Then what are we supposed to do?

925
00:58:05,583 --> 00:58:08,708
The more serious he is about this,
the more careful we need to be.

926
00:58:08,708 --> 00:58:10,683
Yumi's the older one here.

927
00:58:13,792 --> 00:58:16,583
Let's not repeat the same mistakes as before.

928
00:58:16,583 --> 00:58:18,850
This is already the third proposal.

929
00:58:35,417 --> 00:58:37,267
It's raining.

930
00:58:57,417 --> 00:58:59,293
[PD Shin]

931
00:59:07,042 --> 00:59:08,523
Oh, Soon Rok.

932
00:59:08,523 --> 00:59:10,042
<i>Noona.</i>

933
00:59:10,042 --> 00:59:12,417
You made it okay? Are you on the flight?

934
00:59:12,417 --> 00:59:13,780
<i>No.</i>

935
00:59:13,780 --> 00:59:14,792
Then where are you?

936
00:59:14,792 --> 00:59:17,500
<i>I'm right outside your place.</i>

937
00:59:17,500 --> 00:59:19,100
What?

938
00:59:23,273 --> 00:59:24,958
The flight

939
00:59:24,958 --> 00:59:26,875
got cancelled because of an engine problem.

940
00:59:26,875 --> 00:59:29,315
They said I'd have to take
a different one tomorrow, so I came back.

941
00:59:29,315 --> 00:59:31,333
Oh my, how does something
like that even happen?

942
00:59:31,333 --> 00:59:34,125
Is it okay if I come up for a bit?

943
00:59:34,125 --> 00:59:36,125
<i>Of course, get in here.</i>

944
00:59:36,125 --> 00:59:38,017
Okay, I'm heading up.

945
00:59:43,000 --> 00:59:44,933
Thank you.

946
00:59:47,773 --> 00:59:50,250
He's coming back for an answer to the proposal!

947
00:59:50,250 --> 00:59:51,458
What do we do?

948
00:59:51,458 --> 00:59:54,042
I thought we finally
had some breathing room to think.

949
00:59:54,042 --> 00:59:55,458
What is she supposed to say?

950
00:59:55,458 --> 00:59:58,350
Yumi still hasn't figured out what she wants!

951
01:00:02,417 --> 01:00:03,750
Noona.

952
01:00:03,750 --> 01:00:05,500
You got soaked?

953
01:00:05,500 --> 01:00:07,917
I should've come down with an umbrella.

954
01:00:07,917 --> 01:00:10,517
- Hold on, let me grab you a towel.
- Sure.

955
01:00:29,708 --> 01:00:30,740
Thanks.

956
01:00:30,740 --> 01:00:33,267
All that back and forth must've worn you out.

957
01:00:33,898 --> 01:00:35,625
I'm exhausted.

958
01:00:35,625 --> 01:00:37,167
Are you hungry at all?

959
01:00:37,167 --> 01:00:40,350
Actually, do you have anything cold to drink?

960
01:00:41,500 --> 01:00:44,225
- Want me to make you an ade?
- Oh, that sounds great.

961
01:00:46,792 --> 01:00:48,833
What time do you have to leave tomorrow?

962
01:00:48,833 --> 01:00:52,042
It's a morning flight.
I need to be out the door by six.

963
01:00:52,042 --> 01:00:54,017
Oh, that's the middle of the night.

964
01:00:55,292 --> 01:00:57,475
I'll drive you tomorrow.

965
01:01:05,083 --> 01:01:06,457
Noona.

966
01:01:07,500 --> 01:01:09,083
This ring...

967
01:01:09,083 --> 01:01:11,017
should I return it?

968
01:01:13,291 --> 01:01:16,023
- What?
- If it's too much pressure for you,

969
01:01:16,023 --> 01:01:17,542
returning it

970
01:01:17,542 --> 01:01:19,225
is totally fine.

971
01:01:25,708 --> 01:01:26,750
Why would you...

972
01:01:26,750 --> 01:01:29,167
I bought it
because I was swept up in how I felt.

973
01:01:29,167 --> 01:01:32,017
It seemed like it was putting too much on you.

974
01:01:35,625 --> 01:01:37,250
If you're not ready yet,

975
01:01:37,250 --> 01:01:40,433
I can wait.

976
01:01:41,750 --> 01:01:43,958
I just...

977
01:01:43,958 --> 01:01:47,792
I was so sure we'd end up getting married

978
01:01:47,792 --> 01:01:50,792
that I bought it without thinking it through.

979
01:01:50,792 --> 01:01:52,476
That kind of certainty...

980
01:01:54,250 --> 01:01:56,850
where does it even come from?

981
01:01:57,583 --> 01:02:01,683
We haven't even been together a month.

982
01:02:02,708 --> 01:02:06,100
We barely know each other yet.

983
01:02:07,000 --> 01:02:10,017
How can you be that sure?

984
01:02:12,125 --> 01:02:14,583
Without that certainty,

985
01:02:14,583 --> 01:02:16,933
I wouldn't have run back to you
in the first place.

986
01:02:21,092 --> 01:02:23,350
Without it,

987
01:02:24,000 --> 01:02:25,600
back then...

988
01:02:28,292 --> 01:02:30,231
<i>PD Shin?</i>

989
01:02:30,231 --> 01:02:32,933
I never would've come back to find you.

990
01:02:34,083 --> 01:02:36,367
So you've been this certain

991
01:02:36,367 --> 01:02:38,625
since back then?

992
01:02:38,625 --> 01:02:39,680
Yes.

993
01:02:39,680 --> 01:02:41,167
And that certainty,

994
01:02:41,167 --> 01:02:43,417
where exactly is it coming from?

995
01:02:43,417 --> 01:02:45,625
Because I can just tell.

996
01:02:45,625 --> 01:02:47,292
How can you tell?

997
01:02:47,292 --> 01:02:49,267
You're asking me how I know?

998
01:02:51,667 --> 01:02:53,600
In my whole life,

999
01:02:54,708 --> 01:02:58,350
nothing has ever felt like this before.

1000
01:03:01,667 --> 01:03:03,767
So yeah. I know.

1001
01:03:54,500 --> 01:03:58,035
<i>The reason love always catches you off guard</i>

1002
01:03:59,333 --> 01:04:03,475
<i>is that no two loves are ever the same shape.</i>

1003
01:04:05,625 --> 01:04:07,667
<i>So the thing is,</i>

1004
01:04:07,667 --> 01:04:11,100
<i>Soon Rok is a different person entirely.</i>

1005
01:04:12,065 --> 01:04:15,875
<i>"What's the point
of projecting my past experiences</i>

1006
01:04:15,875 --> 01:04:19,766
<i>onto a man who has
a completely different take on love?"</i>

1007
01:04:20,417 --> 01:04:23,308
<i>That was the thought that landed.</i>

1008
01:04:39,458 --> 01:04:41,433
Okay, Soon Rok.

1009
01:04:43,167 --> 01:04:45,350
Let's do it your way.

1010
01:04:46,401 --> 01:04:48,017
Sorry, what?

1011
01:04:49,750 --> 01:04:51,875
The ring,

1012
01:04:51,875 --> 01:04:53,600
let's return it.

1013
01:04:54,856 --> 01:04:56,683
I like you

1014
01:04:57,375 --> 01:05:00,100
so much right now,

1015
01:05:01,292 --> 01:05:04,308
but I think I still need more time.

1016
01:05:05,583 --> 01:05:09,642
There's a responsibility
I feel to get this right.

1017
01:05:10,542 --> 01:05:13,958
- You don't have to feel that...
- So,

1018
01:05:13,958 --> 01:05:16,267
when the time comes,

1019
01:05:17,167 --> 01:05:19,142
I'll be the one to say it.

1020
01:05:21,417 --> 01:05:22,875
Okay.

1021
01:05:22,875 --> 01:05:26,273
But the ring,

1022
01:05:26,273 --> 01:05:28,292
I really think we should return it.

1023
01:05:28,292 --> 01:05:31,167
It's already bought.
Just keep it. It's a birthday gift.

1024
01:05:31,167 --> 01:05:33,833
For a birthday present, this is way too much.

1025
01:05:33,833 --> 01:05:38,058
Every single day I'd feel uneasy having it.

1026
01:05:42,042 --> 01:05:45,917
You're leaving early tomorrow,
so hand me the receipt.

1027
01:05:45,917 --> 01:05:47,167
I'll take care of returning it.

1028
01:05:47,167 --> 01:05:49,000
- But...
- Instead,

1029
01:05:49,000 --> 01:05:52,250
let's take that trip again.

1030
01:05:52,250 --> 01:05:54,558
Doesn't that sound better?

1031
01:06:14,375 --> 01:06:15,792
Are you upset?

1032
01:06:15,792 --> 01:06:17,375
Not at all.

1033
01:06:17,375 --> 01:06:18,708
You seem like you are though.

1034
01:06:18,708 --> 01:06:20,750
I'm not upset, I just...

1035
01:06:20,750 --> 01:06:22,167
Just what?

1036
01:06:22,167 --> 01:06:23,933
I just feel...

1037
01:06:24,875 --> 01:06:26,850
drained.

1038
01:06:32,708 --> 01:06:34,792
Honestly, thank you.

1039
01:06:34,792 --> 01:06:37,833
Just the fact that you were willing
to spend that much on me.

1040
01:06:37,833 --> 01:06:39,000
That alone means everything.

1041
01:06:39,000 --> 01:06:41,875
But it feels like such a waste.

1042
01:06:41,875 --> 01:06:44,142
I'm sorry if that stings.

1043
01:06:48,125 --> 01:06:50,208
I really am touched, you know.

1044
01:06:50,208 --> 01:06:52,183
I mean it.

1045
01:06:53,773 --> 01:06:55,517
One more time.

1046
01:07:01,042 --> 01:07:02,850
One more time.

1047
01:07:07,458 --> 01:07:09,750
And you're still running on empty?

1048
01:07:09,750 --> 01:07:13,042
I'm getting there... but...

1049
01:07:13,042 --> 01:07:15,850
What am I supposed to do with you?

1050
01:07:20,583 --> 01:07:21,708
Still not enough?

1051
01:07:21,708 --> 01:07:23,558
Obviously not.

1052
01:07:36,792 --> 01:07:38,981
So,

1053
01:07:38,981 --> 01:07:41,500
roughly how much more time are we talking?

1054
01:07:41,500 --> 01:07:42,625
Let me think...

1055
01:07:42,625 --> 01:07:44,625
Maybe...

1056
01:07:44,625 --> 01:07:46,042
A year?

1057
01:07:46,042 --> 01:07:47,542
A year?

1058
01:07:47,542 --> 01:07:49,767
Oh, a year is way too long.

1059
01:07:57,708 --> 01:08:01,208
What about six months? That's plenty, isn't it?

1060
01:08:01,208 --> 01:08:04,142
I tend to need time to think things through...

1061
01:08:09,143 --> 01:08:11,417
Nine months then?

1062
01:08:11,417 --> 01:08:13,875
Are you seriously negotiating
with me right now?

1063
01:08:13,875 --> 01:08:16,083
What if we tied it to an anniversary?

1064
01:08:16,083 --> 01:08:17,208
Like Christmas Eve, or...

1065
01:08:17,208 --> 01:08:19,667
Christmas Eve is only a few months away.

1066
01:08:19,667 --> 01:08:21,417
Or, Valentine's Day.

1067
01:08:21,417 --> 01:08:22,458
Oh, my birthday.

1068
01:08:22,458 --> 01:08:25,042
No. That's too far out.

1069
01:08:25,042 --> 01:08:27,125
Oh, the day we first met.

1070
01:08:27,125 --> 01:08:28,808
Let's make it that one...

1071
01:08:44,833 --> 01:08:47,106
Who's that?

1072
01:08:47,106 --> 01:08:48,565
No idea.

1073
01:08:48,565 --> 01:08:50,792
<i>Yumi.</i>

1074
01:08:50,792 --> 01:08:52,433
Mom!

1075
01:08:59,375 --> 01:09:01,167
Is she not home?

1076
01:09:03,333 --> 01:09:05,833
The lights were on.

1077
01:09:05,833 --> 01:09:07,125
Right?

1078
01:09:07,125 --> 01:09:09,017
<i>Yumi!</i>

1079
01:09:10,875 --> 01:09:12,292
<i>Yumi!</i>

1080
01:09:12,292 --> 01:09:14,208
<i>Come on, open up!</i>

1081
01:09:14,208 --> 01:09:16,500
Dad! You came too?

1082
01:09:16,500 --> 01:09:18,458
<i>Yeah, now open the door.</i>

1083
01:09:18,458 --> 01:09:20,725
Oh, just give me a second.

1084
01:09:21,333 --> 01:09:22,375
Hide.

1085
01:09:22,375 --> 01:09:23,606
Hide...

1086
01:09:23,606 --> 01:09:24,750
You want me to hide?

1087
01:09:24,750 --> 01:09:26,958
If they see you here at this hour,

1088
01:09:26,958 --> 01:09:28,690
it'll ruin your first impression. No way!

1089
01:09:28,690 --> 01:09:30,481
Come on...

1090
01:09:30,481 --> 01:09:31,681
This is a bit much...

1091
01:09:31,681 --> 01:09:34,023
- You won't be able to fix it after.
- But...

1092
01:09:34,023 --> 01:09:35,250
Get in there, now!

1093
01:09:35,250 --> 01:09:37,058
Oh, Noona...

1094
01:09:43,458 --> 01:09:44,958
Mom, Dad!

1095
01:09:44,958 --> 01:09:47,042
Yumi.

1096
01:09:47,042 --> 01:09:48,542
What took you so long to answer?

1097
01:09:48,542 --> 01:09:52,208
I was in the bathroom.
But seriously, why didn't you call first?

1098
01:09:52,208 --> 01:09:53,794
We were on our way back from your aunt's

1099
01:09:53,794 --> 01:09:57,375
when your dad just kept insisting we stop by.

1100
01:09:57,375 --> 01:10:00,250
Showing up like this without any notice.
She doesn't like it, you know.

1101
01:10:00,250 --> 01:10:02,292
I missed my daughter.

1102
01:10:02,292 --> 01:10:03,917
Am I not allowed to drop by
my own daughter's place?

1103
01:10:03,917 --> 01:10:06,292
Oh, of course you can. Dad gets a pass. Always.

1104
01:10:06,292 --> 01:10:08,333
- Right?
- Of course.

1105
01:10:08,333 --> 01:10:11,083
- Always.
- What's all this, Dad?

1106
01:10:11,083 --> 01:10:12,375
All the things you like.

1107
01:10:12,375 --> 01:10:14,208
Oh, you got completely soaked.

1108
01:10:14,208 --> 01:10:17,667
This is expensive leather, and it's drenched.
What do I do with this?

1109
01:10:22,833 --> 01:10:25,142
What's this?

1110
01:10:29,333 --> 01:10:31,267
What are you talking about?

1111
01:10:31,875 --> 01:10:34,392
Oh my, what kind of ring is this?

1112
01:10:35,958 --> 01:10:38,475
This looks like a diamond.

1113
01:10:39,208 --> 01:10:40,417
This...

1114
01:10:40,417 --> 01:10:41,958
this isn't an engagement ring, is it?

1115
01:10:41,958 --> 01:10:43,125
What is this?

1116
01:10:43,125 --> 01:10:44,792
Yumi!

1117
01:10:44,792 --> 01:10:47,333
This is an engagement ring, isn't it?

1118
01:10:47,333 --> 01:10:49,083
Did someone give this to you?

1119
01:10:49,083 --> 01:10:50,875
- From who?
- Oh, Mom!

1120
01:10:50,875 --> 01:10:52,376
- Wait...
- Mom!

1121
01:10:52,376 --> 01:10:53,875
- Oh, it's nothing!
- Hey!

1122
01:10:53,875 --> 01:10:55,458
An engagement ring?

1123
01:10:55,458 --> 01:10:58,065
Who gave you this?
Have you been seeing someone?

1124
01:10:58,065 --> 01:10:59,917
No, it's not like that!

1125
01:10:59,917 --> 01:11:01,500
This...

1126
01:11:01,500 --> 01:11:04,292
This is absolutely a diamond.
And this is absolutely an engagement ring.

1127
01:11:04,292 --> 01:11:07,208
What diamond? It's cubic zirconia, Mom.

1128
01:11:07,208 --> 01:11:09,106
Yumi, this...

1129
01:11:09,106 --> 01:11:11,784
- This is a diamond, isn't it?
- Hold on, let me see.

1130
01:11:12,856 --> 01:11:14,792
It's a diamond, alright. It is!

1131
01:11:14,792 --> 01:11:17,125
This is definitely a diamond!

1132
01:11:17,125 --> 01:11:18,708
Who gave this to you?

1133
01:11:18,708 --> 01:11:21,875
What does this guy do? How old is he?

1134
01:11:21,875 --> 01:11:23,250
Take a closer look.

1135
01:11:23,250 --> 01:11:25,583
It's cubic zirconia.
How could this be a diamond?

1136
01:11:25,583 --> 01:11:29,148
Things are really snowballing here.

1137
01:11:29,148 --> 01:11:32,648
Now that Mom and Dad have seen it, it's over.

1138
01:11:32,648 --> 01:11:34,417
It's done.

1139
01:11:34,417 --> 01:11:37,036
I'd say they're getting married
within the year.

1140
01:11:41,625 --> 01:11:43,208
Oh my!

1141
01:11:45,523 --> 01:11:46,833
Who...

1142
01:11:46,833 --> 01:11:48,808
who are you?

1143
01:11:51,208 --> 01:11:53,833
Hello, it's a pleasure to meet you.

1144
01:11:53,833 --> 01:11:57,457
I'm Shin Soon Rok, Yumi's boyfriend.

1145
01:12:00,583 --> 01:12:02,083
Surprise!

1146
01:12:02,083 --> 01:12:03,750
You weren't expecting that, were you?

1147
01:12:03,750 --> 01:12:07,731
Say hi, Mom and Dad.
This is Soon Rok, my boyfriend.

1148
01:12:07,731 --> 01:12:11,308
Hello, it's wonderful to meet you both.

1149
01:12:13,208 --> 01:12:16,125
Oh, so nice to meet you. I'm Yumi's mom.

1150
01:12:16,125 --> 01:12:17,750
It's a pleasure.

1151
01:12:17,750 --> 01:12:18,833
He works in...

1152
01:12:18,833 --> 01:12:21,333
Looks like Mom's already won over, doesn't it?

1153
01:12:21,333 --> 01:12:23,667
Yumi's mom is a total sucker
for a good-looking face.

1154
01:12:23,667 --> 01:12:27,458
Think it might happen even sooner than a year?

1155
01:12:27,458 --> 01:12:30,833
I'll bet it happens before the six-month mark.

1156
01:12:30,833 --> 01:12:34,292
My money's on before Christmas Eve.

1157
01:12:34,292 --> 01:12:35,750
Beaded dress?

1158
01:12:35,750 --> 01:12:38,083
No, silk. Silk would be stunning, right?

1159
01:12:38,083 --> 01:12:41,542
- I'm Yumi's dad.
- Oh, yes.

1160
01:12:41,542 --> 01:12:42,875
Great to meet you, sir.

1161
01:12:42,875 --> 01:12:45,308
Oh, come on, Mom.

1162
01:12:47,750 --> 01:12:49,875
What's gotten into you!

1163
01:12:49,875 --> 01:12:52,690
- Oh, hold on!
- Oh, sir!

1164
01:12:52,690 --> 01:12:54,568
That's got to hurt.

1165
01:13:05,208 --> 01:13:07,475
That's exactly the look I was picturing.

1166
01:13:10,196 --> 01:13:11,708
[Kim Yumi]
<i>I'm Kim Yumi.</i>

1167
01:13:11,708 --> 01:13:13,336
[Kim Go Eun]

1168
01:13:15,708 --> 01:13:17,250
Yes.

1169
01:13:20,417 --> 01:13:21,917
I think I like you.

1170
01:13:21,917 --> 01:13:23,042
[Shin Soon Rok]

1171
01:13:23,042 --> 01:13:24,750
[Kim Jae Won]

1172
01:13:24,750 --> 01:13:27,125
He's incredibly steady and level-headed.

1173
01:13:27,125 --> 01:13:29,000
Do well. Go for it!

1174
01:13:29,000 --> 01:13:30,000
[An Dae Yong]

1175
01:13:30,000 --> 01:13:32,350
[Jeon Seok Ho]

1176
01:13:34,148 --> 01:13:35,273
Writer Kim!

1177
01:13:35,273 --> 01:13:36,667
I want to make this work with you.

1178
01:13:36,667 --> 01:13:37,792
[Kim Ju Ho]

1179
01:13:37,792 --> 01:13:39,750
[Choi Daniel]

1180
01:13:39,750 --> 01:13:40,833
Homebody.

1181
01:13:40,833 --> 01:13:43,708
A handsome PD is here.

1182
01:13:43,708 --> 01:13:47,023
- Okay, one butler secured.
- Yumi.

1183
01:13:47,023 --> 01:13:48,542
Hey, wait just a second!

1184
01:13:48,542 --> 01:13:50,183
Seriously.

1185
01:13:55,833 --> 01:13:57,292
[A One-Sided Love Has Begun]

1186
01:14:38,208 --> 01:14:39,458
Smile.

1187
01:14:39,458 --> 01:14:41,683
Yumi, come on. Smile.

1188
01:14:46,042 --> 01:14:47,708
Alright everyone, it's time.

1189
01:14:47,708 --> 01:14:49,375
Gather up!

1190
01:14:49,375 --> 01:14:51,701
She looks incredible.

1191
01:14:53,708 --> 01:14:57,315
- Soon Rok, take a breath.
- Soon Rok looks great.

1192
01:14:57,315 --> 01:14:58,792
Let's smile!

1193
01:14:59,833 --> 01:15:01,042
Love Cell.

1194
01:15:01,042 --> 01:15:03,350
Hey, Love Cell...

1195
01:15:04,833 --> 01:15:06,708
Shorter people, please come to the front.

1196
01:15:06,708 --> 01:15:08,792
Yes, the person on the left,
could you move just a little more?

1197
01:15:08,792 --> 01:15:10,356
Stop blocking me. I'm not even in the shot.

1198
01:15:10,356 --> 01:15:12,042
Let's wrap this up. I'm ready to eat.

1199
01:15:12,042 --> 01:15:13,333
Alright, here we go.

1200
01:15:13,333 --> 01:15:15,333
- This is good.
- One, two.

1201
01:15:15,333 --> 01:15:18,314
- Yumi.
- Yumi.

1202
01:15:21,690 --> 01:15:24,225
I hope this turns out well.

1203
01:15:26,458 --> 01:15:28,625
Man, I'm so damn happy.

1204
01:15:28,625 --> 01:15:30,808
This is so damn good.

1205
01:15:37,667 --> 01:15:40,023
Not letting go this time!

1206
01:15:40,023 --> 01:15:41,917
- For life.
- I'm nervous.

1207
01:15:41,917 --> 01:15:43,792
<i>♪ Lullaby, lullaby ♪</i>

1208
01:15:43,792 --> 01:15:45,625
Reel in the big one!

1209
01:15:46,417 --> 01:15:47,500
I could burst!

1210
01:15:47,500 --> 01:15:48,542
[Deep Inside the Heart]

1211
01:15:49,208 --> 01:15:51,767
I'm Ung's Love Cell.

1212
01:15:52,847 --> 01:15:54,833
Sinsaimdang.

1213
01:15:54,833 --> 01:15:57,083
<i>♪ I want to buy this ♪</i>

1214
01:15:57,083 --> 01:15:59,192
What's the point of saving every penny!

1215
01:15:59,192 --> 01:16:00,651
Fashion Cell is guilty!

1216
01:16:00,651 --> 01:16:01,667
It's effortless style.

1217
01:16:01,667 --> 01:16:03,875
- Okay, everyone.
- That's hilarious.

1218
01:16:03,875 --> 01:16:05,667
It's Hysterical Cell!

1219
01:16:05,667 --> 01:16:07,792
We keep it cool.

1220
01:16:07,792 --> 01:16:09,833
Oh, it's a sweet story.

1221
01:16:09,833 --> 01:16:12,125
It's here. My instincts are firing again!

1222
01:16:12,125 --> 01:16:13,583
A kiss.

1223
01:16:13,583 --> 01:16:15,875
There's a proper order to things in this world.

1224
01:16:15,875 --> 01:16:17,625
And her skin looks flawless too.

1225
01:16:17,625 --> 01:16:19,356
Time to go recharge.

1226
01:16:19,356 --> 01:16:23,058
There's always a separate compartment
for dessert, so don't worry.

1227
01:16:23,667 --> 01:16:26,600
It's okay to push a little here.

1228
01:16:27,815 --> 01:16:30,392
Haven't written a scenario
like this in a while.

1229
01:16:40,667 --> 01:16:41,898
[Right-Hand Cell lands on Planet H2 alone]

1230
01:16:41,898 --> 01:16:44,017
You're saying it's nothing?

1231
01:17:00,083 --> 01:17:01,940
Love X-ray!

1232
01:17:01,940 --> 01:17:03,292
I'm here.

1233
01:17:03,292 --> 01:17:04,317
[Naughty Cell]

1234
01:17:04,317 --> 01:17:06,225
You look really pretty today, noona.

1235
01:17:17,292 --> 01:17:20,725
There's only one main lead in this world.

1236
01:17:27,481 --> 01:17:29,042
- Bye!
- Bye!

1237
01:17:29,042 --> 01:17:32,476
- Bye!
- Bye!
